@startuml fig-ssh-port-forwarding
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title SSH Port Forwarding: Local, Remote and Dynamic

participant "User\napplication" as U #FFE0B2
participant "Client\nmachine" as C #BBDEFB
participant "SSH Server\n(bastion)" as B #E1BEE7
participant "Internal service\n(DB / HTTP)" as I #C8E6C9

== LOCAL FORWARDING (-L) ==

U -> C : connect localhost:9000
C -[#1565C0]> B : SSH tunnel (encrypted)
B -> I : connect internal:5432
note right of B
  ssh -L 9000:internal:5432 bastion
  Access remote services via local port
end note

== REMOTE FORWARDING (-R) ==

U -> B : connect bastion:9000
B -[#1565C0]> C : SSH tunnel (encrypted)
C -> I : connect localhost:3000
note right of C
  ssh -R 9000:localhost:3000 bastion
  Expose a local service through the server
end note

== DYNAMIC FORWARDING (-D) ==

U -> C : browser SOCKS → localhost:1080
C -[#1565C0]> B : SSH SOCKS tunnel
B -> I : dynamic destination
note right of B
  ssh -D 1080 bastion
  General-purpose encrypted proxy
end note

legend right
  Local: local port → tunnel → remote target
  Remote: remote port → tunnel → local target
  Dynamic: SOCKS proxy via tunnel to any host
  All three modes reuse the SSH connection.
endlegend
@enduml
